                    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Flag_of_Ethiopia.svg/510px-Flag_of_Ethiopia.svg.png")
c13 = Country.create!(name: "Finland",
                    overview: "Finland, a Nordic country known for its lakes and forests, embodies a unique blend of modern design, technology, and a deep connection to nature. With a rich folklore and a tradition of saunas, Finland celebrates its heritage through festivals, contemporary architecture, and a strong emphasis on education.",
                    culinary: "Finnish cuisine is influenced by the country's natural resources, with a focus on fish, berries, and game meats. Traditional dishes include karjalanpiirakka (Karelian pasty), kalakukko (fish and pork pie), and hernekeitto (pea soup). The use of fresh, seasonal ingredients and a connection to nature are integral to Finnish culinary traditions.",
