# Georgia 14
c14.breads << Bread.create!(name: "Khachapuri (Georgian Cheese Bread)",
                            description: "Khachapuri, Georgia's beloved cheese-filled bread, varies by region, with the Adjaruli version being an open-faced delight filled with cheese and herbs, topped with an egg. This recipe uses bread flour for an easier-to-handle dough, creating a sturdy base for the rich filling, making it perfect for breakfast or lunch gatherings.",
                            ingredients: ["43g unsalted butter", "227g milk", "6g granulated sugar or 9g non-diastatic malt powder", "0.5 teaspoon coriander", "9g table salt for dough", "2 teaspoons instant yeast or active dry yeast", "330g King Arthur Unbleached Bread Flour for dough", "227g mozzarella cheese or Muenster cheese, shredded", "113g ricotta cheese", "57g crumbled feta cheese", "1 large egg for filling", "14g Bread Flour for filling", "0.5 teaspoon table salt for filling", "0.5 to 1 teaspoon coarsely ground black pepper", "2 tablespoons coarsely chopped flat-leaf parsley", "2 tablespoons finely chopped chives", "1 large egg beaten with 1 teaspoon water for egg wash", "4 large eggs, cold for garnish", "4 teaspoons butter for garnish"],
                            instructions: ["Heat butter and milk until butter melts. Mix sugar (or malt powder), coriander, and salt in a bowl; add hot milk to dissolve sugar. Cool to lukewarm.", "Add yeast and flour, mixing to a shaggy mass. Rest covered for 10 minutes. Knead until smooth, adding 1-2 tablespoons flour if sticky.", "Let dough rise in a greased bowl, covered, for 1-1.5 hours until increased by at least one third.", "Combine all filling ingredients, leaving some cheese bits intact. Divide risen dough into four, roll each into 10\"x6\" ovals, and let rest 15 minutes.", "Spoon filling onto each dough oval, leaving 1\" edge. Fold edges over cheese, twisting ends to form a boat shape. Let rise 20 minutes.", "Preheat oven to 375°F. Brush dough with egg wash and bake for 15-20 minutes until set.", "Make an indentation in each khachapuri, add an egg and a teaspoon of butter, and bake for another 8-15 minutes depending on desired egg doneness.", "Serve warm, garnished with fresh herbs. Store leftovers in the refrigerator for up to five days."],
                            imageUrl: "https://i.redd.it/8mjgi45g21o91.jpg",
                            country_id: c14.id)
c14.breads << Bread.create!(name: "Kubdari (Georgian: კუბდარი)",
                            description: "Kubdari is a traditional Georgian meat-filled pastry originating from the Svaneti region. Known locally as 'kuptaari', it's a savory dish that can be made with beef, pork, or a combination of both, using cubed meat rather than minced for a juicier filling. Seasoned with a blend of spices including cumin, dill, coriander, blue fenugreek, and red pepper, Kubdari offers a robust flavor encased in a sturdy pastry. This recipe provides a step-by-step guide to creating this Georgian culinary staple, perfect for a hearty meal any time of the day.",
                            ingredients: ["Filling: 500g pork, 500g young beef, 1 medium onion, 2 cloves garlic, 1/3 tsp powdered cumin, 1/4 tsp powdered dill, 1 tsp dried coriander, 1/2 tsp blue fenugreek, 1 tsp red pepper, Salt to taste", "Dough: 900g flour, 400ml warm water, 1 tbs yeast, 1 tsp sugar, 1 tsp salt, 1 egg (optional), 200g all-purpose flour for dusting and kneading, Butter for glazing"],
                            instructions: ["For the filling, cube the beef and pork. Finely chop the onion and garlic. Mix these with the spices and salt in a bowl, using hands to ensure the meat is well seasoned.", "Prepare the dough by dissolving yeast in 400ml warm water. In a separate bowl, create a well in 900g flour, add the yeast mixture, egg (optional), and sugar. Mix to form a soft dough ball.", "Cover the dough and let it rise in a warm place for 2 hours. Knead with an additional 150g flour until firm.", "Divide the dough into 4 pieces, mold into balls, and let rest for 10 minutes under cling film.", "Roll out each dough ball and add the filling, wrap the dough around the filling, sealing it at the top.", "Press the filled dough into circular shapes, less than 20cm in diameter, on a flour-dusted baking tray. Avoid flattening too much.", "Bake at 200°C until the dough turns golden brown and the meat cooks in its juices.", "Glaze each Kubdari with butter and serve hot."],
                            imageUrl: "imageUrl:”https://i.redd.it/ht5ootgsoq8a1.jpg",
                            country_id: c14.id)

# Germany 15
c15.breads << Bread.create!(name: "German Bread (Bauernbrot)",
                            description: "Experience the authentic taste of Bavarian sourdough bread with this traditional German recipe. Crafted to emulate the flavors of bread baked in old stone ovens of small villages, this recipe offers a hearty, delicious loaf perfect for any bread lover. With a process spread over two days, this bread's deep flavors and perfect texture are a testament to the art of German baking.",
                            ingredients: ["42g compressed fresh yeast", "946ml warm water, divided", "25g white sugar, divided", "480g all-purpose flour, divided", "960g white rye flour", "30g salt"],
                            instructions: ["Begin with the sourdough starter by crumbling the yeast into a large bowl. Whisk in 946ml of warm water and 25g of sugar until dissolved. Gradually whisk in 240g of all-purpose flour until smooth. Cover with a dish towel and let sit at room temperature for 24 hours.", "After 24 hours, stir the starter well, cover, and let stand for another 24 hours to develop.", "Combine the rye flour, the remaining 240g of all-purpose flour, salt, and the remaining sugar in a large bowl. Mix in the sourdough starter with a wooden spoon, then stir in 473ml of warm water.", "Knead the dough on a floured surface for 15 to 20 minutes until smooth, adding a little water if too stiff. Place the dough in a large bowl, cover, and let rise until doubled, about 1 to 2 hours.", "Knead the risen dough for 5 minutes to activate the gluten. Shape into 1 or 2 long loaves on baking sheets. Let rise for about 1 hour.", "Preheat the oven to 220°C (425°F). Bake for 45 minutes for 2 loaves or 1 1/2 hours for a large loaf, until the crust is dark and the bread is well-baked. Cool completely before slicing. Optionally, freeze half for later use.", "For extra starter, mix 240g all-purpose flour and 473ml water into the starter on the second day and let stand for another 24 hours. Use half for the bread and save the rest. Adjustments may be needed for humidity and heat. If conditions are too humid and hot, consider starting the bread early in the morning."],
                            imageUrl: "https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5b00599f620b85f994d55ade/1616071245788-AT2AJE6B7N5UFYE0C3PQ/Bauernbrot+f%C3%BCr+Anf%C3%A4nger-3708-Bearbeitet.jpg",
                            country_id: c15.id)
c15.breads << Bread.create!(name: "German-Style Pretzels",
                            description: "This pretzel recipe is inspired by traditional German baking techniques, offering a delightful taste and texture. Perfect for those who appreciate the authentic, chewy crust and soft interior of a classic pretzel.",
                            ingredients: ["614g Unbleached Bread Flour", "333g water", "12g table salt", "1 1/4 teaspoons instant yeast", "28g butter, soft", "1/4 teaspoon diastatic malt powder (optional)", "For the water bath:", "1361g water", "36g baking soda", "For topping (optional):", "Coarse sea salt, kosher salt, or pretzel salt"],
                            instructions: ["Mix all dough ingredients in a mixing bowl or stand mixer bowl. Knead to make a supple, elastic dough. If using a stand mixer, mix on low for 3 minutes, then medium for about 5 minutes.", "Cover the bowl and let the dough rise for 45 minutes. Perform a fold by running a scraper down the inside wall of the bowl, folding the dough over on itself, and turning the bowl 90°; repeat three more times. Let rise for another 45 minutes.", "Deflate the dough gently, divide into 10 pieces (about 100g each), shape each into a rough log, cover, and let rest for 20 minutes.", "Roll each piece into an 18” to 22”-long rope and shape into pretzels. Place on lightly greased or parchment-lined baking sheets, cover, and let rest for 30 minutes, then refrigerate for 60 minutes.", "Preheat the oven to 450°F (232°C). Prepare the water bath by boiling the water and baking soda.", "Boil 3 or 4 pretzels at a time for 1 minute, then return to baking sheets. Slash each pretzel horizontally across its base.", "Sprinkle with salt if desired and bake for 14 to 16 minutes until well-browned. Cool on a rack.", "Store well-wrapped pretzels for up to 3 days on the counter or freeze for longer storage."],
                            imageUrl: "https://redcurrantbakery.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_0751-scaled.jpg",
                            country_id: c15.id)

# Greece 16
c16.breads << Bread.create!(name: "Pita Bread",
                            description: "Discover the joy of making your own Greek pita bread with this simple yet delicious recipe. With just 4 ingredients, you can create fluffy and soft pita bread that's perfect for any meal. Whether you choose to bake them for a crunchy texture or steam for a softer feel, these pitas will become a staple in your kitchen.",
                            ingredients: ["500–530g strong white bread flour or a mix of white and whole-wheat flour", "360g lukewarm water", "3 tsp dry instant yeast", "1 tsp salt", "1 tsp sugar"],
                            instructions: ["Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water and let it froth for 5-10 minutes.", "Add flour and salt to the mixture and knead with a dough hook for 6-8 minutes, or by hand, until it forms an elastic and slightly sticky ball.", "Coat the dough with olive oil, cover with plastic wrap and a towel, and let it rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 20 minutes.", "Divide the dough into 6 balls, each about 145g, and let them rest for 15 minutes for a second proofing.", "Shape each ball into a 20cm diameter circle, using a rolling pin for a crunchier pita or hand-stretching for a softer one. Use your fingertips or a fork to create dimples on the surface.", "For baked pita, cook in a slightly oiled, medium-heat non-stick pan for about 3 minutes each side. Cover with a lid to retain moisture for softer pitas.", "For steamed pita, place the shaped dough on oiled aluminum foil in a pan with a splash of water. Cover and steam for 12-15 minutes, then flip and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes.", "Serve warm for the best experience."],
                            imageUrl: "https://apronandwhisk.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Greek-Pocketless-Pita-Bread-Apron-Whisk-2.jpg",
                            country_id: c16.id)

# Iceland 17
c17.breads << Bread.create!(name: "Icelandic Rye Bread (Rúgbrauð)",
                            description: "This traditional Icelandic rye bread, known for its dense, mildly sweet, and hearty characteristics, is a staple in Iceland. Easy to make with no kneading or rising required, it combines the rich flavors of rye with the sweetness of honey and molasses, perfectly complemented by a tangy touch of buttermilk. Ideal for serving with smoked or pickled foods, or simply enjoying with salted butter.",
                            ingredients: ["477g Organic Medium Rye Flour", "2 teaspoons table salt", "1 tablespoon baking powder", "3/4 teaspoon baking soda", "454g buttermilk", "168g honey", "170g molasses"],
                            instructions: ["Preheat the oven to 325°F (163°C) and position a rack in the center.", "In a large bowl, whisk together the rye flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda.", "In a separate bowl, combine the buttermilk, honey, and molasses.", "Stir the wet ingredients into the dry until well combined.", "Transfer the batter to a lightly greased 9” pain de mie (pullman) pan, smoothing the top. Grease the lid and secure it on the pan.", "Bake for 2 hours, then turn off the oven, remove the pan's lid, and leave the loaf in the oven for an additional 15 minutes.", "Remove from the oven, turn out the bread onto a cooling rack, and allow to cool completely before slicing.", "Serve thinly sliced with butter, or pair with savory toppings like pickled herring, smoked salmon, or cheese."],
                            imageUrl: "https://www.cookingismessy.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/rye_bread.jpg",
                            country_id: c17.id)

