                            instructions: ["Boil the sugar with water until fully dissolved and syrupy. Let it cool.", "In a mixing bowl, combine flour, bread crumbs, milk powder, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, and vanilla. Mix in the egg yolks.", "Gradually add the cooled sugar syrup to the dry ingredients and knead for ten minutes.", "Incorporate the butter into the dough, knead again, then cover and let it rest for 30 minutes.", "Divide the dough into 12 equal parts, shape into ovals, and arrange on a baking tray.", "Brush the tops with water and sprinkle sesame seeds over.", "Bake in a preheated oven at 200°C (392°F) for 20-30 minutes or until done.", "Enjoy Roti Gambang with coffee or tea for breakfast, or pair with a hearty soup for dinner."],
